{#-
name: network-service-hardening
summary: Network listeners must be limited to localhost and tailnet clients.
domain: engineering
audience: agent
severity: default
tags: [network, security, tailscale, hardening]
scope: [any]
phase: [planning, executing, reviewing]
-#}
Any code that listens on a network port must limit access to localhost and the tailnet.

Accept localhost plus Tailscale addresses only:

- IPv4 localhost (`127.0.0.1`) and IPv6 localhost (`::1`)
- Tailscale CGNAT (`100.64.0.0/10`)
- Tailscale IPv6 (`fd7a:115c:a1e0::/48`)

Reject everything else with a terse 403. Binding to `0.0.0.0` is fine when filtering happens in the request handler (more robust than interface binding when Tailscale connects after server start). Separate app-layer auth is optional for local/tailnet-only personal services.
